reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 28, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Small Package, Large and Fast Storage
reviews.reviewText: Bought one of the 32GB ones for work and then decided to get a 64GB for my self, since most of my flash drives are USB2.0. The form factor is great (though I wish it came with a lanyard) and the speed is better than advertised. Build quality looks good. We'll have to see about longevity, but I use a flash drive so seldom that I doubt I will have any issues. I doubt you can do much better for eleven bucks at this time.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very very small
reviews.reviewText: Very very small, but very powerful. I like mine.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 8, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Small in size, no lanyard, but it works just fine.
reviews.reviewText: The price was great for the size and USB 3.0. I use it for my car cameras and it works fine. I save at least 35% off other USB drives.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Strange rating? Here's why
reviews.reviewText: I ordered this because I was looking for something which was truly as small as you can get. This one looked like it was and also offered very good bang for the buck. While I'm not complaining about the device or apparent quality, I dislike that it sticks out further than I expected and so I am disappointed in that regard. There are definitely smaller ones out there but they are more expensive.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I love the metal casing
reviews.reviewText: Works like many others but what I like is that it is metal. I had another brand for about 1 year and eventually, the top cracked off. I trust this will last a long time.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 5, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Small but powerful.
reviews.reviewText: Excellent for data saving and working on the go.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 23, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Flash drive works just fine, but has a severe stuttering issue playing back movies
reviews.reviewText: The drive is actually a solid drive and it does indeed store 128GB worth of data on it. Moving files to and from the flash drive works without a sweat but this is the first flash drive that I've ever had a problem streaming movies stored on it. When I load up 'any' movie and attempt to play it in a video player like Media Player Classic, VLC, or Windows Media Player the video will start stuttering and jerking, the audio will sound completely corrupted, and it will only play back around 3-4fps. I have brought this up with the Gigastone customer service and they attempted to tell me that my computer was the problem and not the flash drive. If it had been 2 days sooner I would have returned the flash drive because it's no good to people like me who like to stream videos directly from flash drives. I now have a drive I can only use for file transfers and because it's a refurbished flash drive I'm not exactly sure how long the drive will even last before it kicks the bucket. I'll probably use it for unimportant storage needs but I do not feel comfortable using Gigastone products any longer and will not be using them in the future.(P.S. This is the second Gigastone flash drive I had issues with. The first flash drive completely failed after 3 weeks which had very important data, and it had to be sent to a data recovery center to get the data removed from it. Luckily I only had to pay around $300 for a complete NAND extraction and recovery, but this final issue is the straw that broke the camel's back.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 1, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Plug-and-Stay USB Thumbdrive
reviews.reviewText: Its perfect. I have a Toughbook, where the external USB Ports are usually covered with weak plastic covers. With this little device, I can plug it into my CF-31 and leave it there as a hard-copy backup to all my work, without worrying about breaking anything. It's super tough and so I've no worries about it breaking and losing my data. I would recommend this product and this buyer to anybody.

reviews.reviewTitle: Almacena y funciona segun lo descrito.
reviews.reviewText: Las aventuras con marcas (para mí) desconocidas suelen funcionar sobre el 50% de probabilidad.En este caso, la marca me ha resultado competente. Me funciona para lo que lo necesito. Pero la diferencia respecto a otros de estilo similar será la que se pueda comprobar en su duracion a la larga.A día de hoy de almacenamiento de configuraciones de teclados (instrumento), que en el caso de uno de ellos, me lo detecta y opera bien; en el otro no. Cuestion de compatibilidades no descritas de los aparatos.Puedo decir que funciona, pero no sé aún de la durabilidad que es lo que más me preocupa , ni tampoco puedo opinar de que sea compatible con todo aparato porque tan sólo lo uso para esa finalidad concreta.

reviews.reviewTitle: Metallkorpus geht nicht so schnell kaputt
reviews.reviewText: Ich habe immer USB-Sticks für den täglichen Gebrauch in meiner Hosentasche. Dabei bricht der Plasikkorpus relativ oft und schnell. Dieser hier aus Metall ist die perfekte und langlebigste Lösung für meine Verwendungszwecke.
El producto cumple con todo lo descrito, lo volveré a comprar

reviews.reviewTitle: No se nota en el ordenador
reviews.reviewText: Gran capacidad en poco espacio. Para mí, lo más importante es que no sobresale del lateral del portátil, xon lo que, al meterlo en su funda no tengo que extraerlo. En la memira USB guardo toda la documentación y la puedo trasladar de un ordenador a otro como si fuera un disco duro, pero sin sus desventajas.
